snippet.textDisplay: There’s a good lesson here. You can’t buy success. No matter how much money Jerry Jones throws around, if you don’t play as a team, you don’t have a team. It has to come from inside. From your heart. From something besides wanting a championship for your overblown ego. When you make money the symbol of success you take away the desire to win. The worst problem the Cowboys have is Jerry Jones. A good owner creates a good atmosphere for his team. Jones needs to stop pointing the finger at everybody else and point at the mirror.
